{
  "text": "However, if k \u00c3 is miss-estimated, the EM algorithm almost always leads to a poor estimate of \u00c2 \u00c2 \u00c3 . For example, if k > k \u00c3 , the EM will regard a true density as a mixture of two or more densities, and has no mechanism to push those redundant j s toward zero. As a result, the estimate of \u00c2 \u00c2 \u00c3 is poor. To address this problem, papers [CITATION_1] , [CITATION_2] have recently proposed a new learning framework, which gives the ML estimate \u00c2 \u00c2 of \u00c2 \u00c2 \u00c3 via maximizing ",
  "citation_candidates": [
